install node.js
>> npm --> node package manager

install angular-cli

npm install -g @angular/cli

--> isntall a tool called "ng"

ng --version

ng new angular-demo
>> creates a boilerplate demo application with all the config files
1. angular.json
    --> index = "src/index.html"
    --> main = "src/main.ts"

ng serve -o
--> starts a dev server at port 4200
--> watches for changes in src folder
--> on change detection, transpile all ts files into js files
--> refreshes the browser automatically

